<br>
You don't NEED it to pull, but it does help a lot.  Why take a beating when you can avoid being hit?  Besides, for those of us non caster classes, being summoned when firing arrows can hurt.  Sometimes, proximity agro to pull is best.  Sure, it doesn't matter in Velks, when you can just loose an arrow and forget about it, but it does matter in places where survival is a matter of avoiding unnessesary hits.<br>
<br>
Plus, it's darned convenient. <br>
<br>
And for non tank classes, is stamina really worth it?  A 60 rogue gets 4 hps per sta, (less above 255 in the 61-65 range) and I fail to see where 3 points of AA Stamina (6 sta total) for 30 hps is more useful than being able to outrun nearly all mobs.  I mean, I get more than that many hps off a player made Black Saphire Earing.<br>
<br>
Regen is of course useful in all situations, and my next three points will be going there.  But unless you need the bandaids for soloing, or you're a pure tank who isn't at the stamina cap, I fail to see the point of taking anything other than Run 3 and Regen 3 (even wisdom can be capped... Regen is never capped, and Run 3 is often in effect.  Once you've got enough wisdom gear to hit cap, those AA points you spent are wasted.  Regen and run speed are never wasted points)<br>
<br>
And yes, I normally pull with a 200 range bow plus 150 range arrows.  But Run 3 still helps.<br>
